KNOWN KERNEL BUGS

 - threading applications can lockup due to a kernel bug
 - vfork is unstable and temporarily disabled
 - attaching to a sleeping process, terminates it
 - stopped process with SIGSTOP/SIGTSTP/SIGTTIN/SIGTTOU does not process SIGCONT from other sources
 - multiple events reported to a debugger in the same time result in reporting a single event and dropping the others
